WEBVTT

00:02.460 --> 00:06.040
Day 6,593
of parenthood.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.080
Odd-numbered day.
You get first pick.

00:08.290 --> 00:09.420
I'll take Anna-Kat.

00:09.420 --> 00:10.750
Okay, I'll check in
on Taylor.

00:10.750 --> 00:12.460
Can you take Oliver?
Uhp!
You know the rule --

00:12.460 --> 00:14.170
when you pick first, you also
have to take Oliver.

00:14.170 --> 00:16.380
Whoever said kids grow up fast
is an idiot.

00:16.380 --> 00:17.750
They grow up slow,
Greg.

00:17.750 --> 00:18.880
Real slow.

00:18.880 --> 00:19.880
[ Chuckles ]

00:19.880 --> 00:25.040
♪♪

00:25.040 --> 00:26.830
Oh, buenas noches,
Mrs. Otto.

00:26.830 --> 00:28.170
Cooper.
You have 10 houses.

00:28.170 --> 00:29.420
Get out of mine.

00:29.420 --> 00:31.170
We're actually having an
important conversation.

00:31.170 --> 00:32.420
Is this conversation
trying to get me

00:32.420 --> 00:33.960
to buy you
that Gucci belt?

00:33.960 --> 00:35.750
Because I'm running out of
curse words to put before "no."

00:35.750 --> 00:37.120
No, actually,

00:37.120 --> 00:38.540
we're talking about
that troubled kid

00:38.540 --> 00:40.000
who called in
to Teen Help Line.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.750
We've got an idea
who it is.

00:41.750 --> 00:43.750
He said everyone
thinks he's Superman.

00:43.750 --> 00:46.040
Well, this kid Trevor's always
wearing a Superman T-shirt.

00:46.040 --> 00:47.920
Shocker -- he doesn't
have any friends.

00:47.920 --> 00:49.380
So, we're going
to befriend him.

00:49.380 --> 00:51.250
I'm actually
proud of you.

00:51.250 --> 00:52.500
I'm proud of us,
too, Mom.

00:52.500 --> 00:53.790
Ugh.

00:53.790 --> 00:55.250
Does that mean you'll buy me
that belt?

00:55.250 --> 00:56.670
[Bleep] you and the horse
you rode in on, you [bleep]

00:56.670 --> 00:57.710
No!

00:58.920 --> 01:00.750
Oh. She found
a new one.

01:00.750 --> 01:04.210
♪♪

01:04.210 --> 01:06.670
Friendly reminder to complete
your life-skills list.

01:06.670 --> 01:08.290
If you don't finish it,
you don't go to prom.

01:08.290 --> 01:09.670
I did
the important ones.

01:09.670 --> 01:11.500
I changed
the windshield-wiper fluid,

01:11.500 --> 01:13.460
and I switched around fruit
stickers at the grocery store.

01:13.460 --> 01:15.880
I got a Honeycrisp for the price
of a Granny Smith.

01:15.880 --> 01:17.420
That one was clearly
your mother's.

01:17.420 --> 01:19.380
Plus, I sent my application
in to Carnegie Mellon,

01:19.380 --> 01:20.710
and I did
my audition tape.

01:20.710 --> 01:22.710
I even noticed I spelled
"Carnegie" wrong,

01:22.710 --> 01:23.790
and then I fixed it.

01:23.790 --> 01:26.000
Then I noticed I spelled
"Mellon" wrong,

01:26.000 --> 01:27.080
and then I fixed that.

01:27.080 --> 01:28.540
And then I saw I spelled
"Carnegie" wrong

01:28.540 --> 01:30.540
in a different way,
and then I fixed that.

01:30.540 --> 01:31.750
[ Chuckling ]
I'm doing great.

01:31.750 --> 01:33.460
Have you prepared for
your alumni interview?

01:33.460 --> 01:35.040
Dude, that's like
a month away!

01:35.040 --> 01:36.830
And yes,
I'm all ready for it.
You mean you --

01:36.830 --> 01:39.120
Yes! Whatever you're about to
say, I did it! I did everything!

01:39.120 --> 01:40.500
Okay!
Stop yelling at me!

01:40.500 --> 01:41.580
Stop making me
yell at you!

01:44.210 --> 01:45.920
Do all your friends yell at
their fathers?

01:45.920 --> 01:47.120
You're getting off easy.

01:47.120 --> 01:49.000
Olivia Andal slaps her dad
in public.

01:49.000 --> 01:53.420
♪♪

01:53.420 --> 01:54.250
Time to get to bed.

01:55.880 --> 01:58.880
First, I need you to sign
a permission slip really quick.

01:58.880 --> 02:00.120
What's it for?

02:00.120 --> 02:01.290
And why are you
showing it to me

02:01.290 --> 02:03.040
like Taylor shows me
her report card?

02:03.040 --> 02:05.500
My new friends invited me to
join their scout troop,

02:05.500 --> 02:06.710
The Wildflower Girls.

02:06.710 --> 02:07.710
That sounds great.

02:07.710 --> 02:09.040
Wait. Do you promise?

02:09.040 --> 02:10.710
Say it.
Say you promise.

02:10.710 --> 02:12.620
Fine. I promise.

02:13.580 --> 02:15.080
Anna-Kat!

02:15.080 --> 02:17.080
Sage, Nancy, and Tara Summers
are the troop leaders.

02:17.080 --> 02:18.210
You know
I can't stand them.

02:18.210 --> 02:20.000
Well, what difference
does it make?

02:20.000 --> 02:21.540
You're not in the troop.
I am.

02:21.540 --> 02:23.670
Because those terrible moms
and their daughters

02:23.670 --> 02:25.620
are bound to be
a bad influence on you.

02:25.620 --> 02:28.330
Plus, they're going to e-mail me
and want me to volunteer,

02:28.330 --> 02:30.420
and I get migraines if I have
to fake smile too long.

02:30.420 --> 02:31.620
Unh-unh. Remember?

02:31.620 --> 02:33.170
You promised.

02:33.170 --> 02:35.170
A mother's promise
means nothing.

02:35.170 --> 02:36.170
Good night.

02:36.170 --> 02:37.580
[ Door closes ]

02:37.580 --> 02:40.790
♪♪

02:40.790 --> 02:42.920
[ Both sigh ]

02:42.920 --> 02:43.960
Taylor's upset with me.

02:43.960 --> 02:45.210
Anna-Kat's upset with me.

02:45.210 --> 02:47.250
How's Oliver?
Regular terrible.

02:47.250 --> 02:48.250
Hmm.

02:48.250 --> 02:49.380
Other than
the Mother's Day gifts

02:49.380 --> 02:51.290
they force them
to make me at school,

02:51.290 --> 02:53.170
I'm not sure what
I'm getting out of all this.

02:53.170 --> 02:54.960
♪♪

02:57.380 --> 03:03.420
♪♪

03:03.420 --> 03:05.290
I'm feeling guilty about
not letting Anna-Kat

03:05.290 --> 03:07.170
sign up
for Wildflower Girls.

03:07.170 --> 03:09.420
At what age can I stop
putting my kids first?

03:09.420 --> 03:10.540
Right when
they can talk.

03:10.540 --> 03:12.380
If you can say "milk,"
you can get it yourself.

03:12.380 --> 03:14.290
My kids
always come first.

03:14.290 --> 03:16.290
Do I miss having
the master bedroom? Sure.

03:16.290 --> 03:18.670
But they wanted a climbing wall.
Who am I to say no?

03:18.670 --> 03:19.880
Uh, their mother.

03:19.880 --> 03:21.380
You're making
your kids soft.

03:21.380 --> 03:23.120
They'd never survive
in the wild.

03:23.120 --> 03:24.920
My kids are not going
to be in the wild.

03:24.920 --> 03:27.080
You don't know that.
People end up in the wild.

03:27.080 --> 03:29.000
Can you guys shut up? I'm trying
to work something out.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.670
I think you should
let Anna-Kat join.

03:30.670 --> 03:32.290
Kids are only young for so long,
and life is hard enough.

03:32.290 --> 03:33.500
Give them
what they want.

03:33.500 --> 03:35.210
Electronics,
video games, candy.

03:35.210 --> 03:36.620
Make it rain.

03:36.620 --> 03:39.290
Don't listen to her, Katie.
You can't give kids everything.

03:39.290 --> 03:40.790
'Cause in the wild,
there's nothing.

03:42.460 --> 03:43.960
Sorry, Doris,
Angela might be right.

03:43.960 --> 03:45.380
[ Gasps ]
Oh.

03:45.380 --> 03:47.040
You mean you're actually
gonna take my suggestion

03:47.040 --> 03:48.290
over hers for once?

03:48.290 --> 03:49.540
Mm-hmm.
Oh.

03:49.540 --> 03:50.920
Excuse me.

03:50.920 --> 03:52.000
[ Clears throat,
chuckles ]

03:52.000 --> 03:53.750
I win! I win!

03:53.750 --> 03:55.250
I win! I win!

03:55.250 --> 03:56.380
You know
that point in life

03:56.380 --> 03:58.040
where you think you've
outgrown your friends?

03:58.040 --> 03:59.120
This is it.

04:00.210 --> 04:02.080
[ Chuckles ]
Take that.

04:02.080 --> 04:06.500
♪♪

04:06.500 --> 04:07.880
Look at that kid.

04:07.880 --> 04:10.250
Gucci belt.
His life must be great.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.880
A Gucci belt doesn't
make you happy.

04:13.170 --> 04:15.920
A limited-edition one worn by
Bradley Cooper at the Oscars.

04:15.920 --> 04:17.040
Now, that's happiness.

04:19.380 --> 04:20.960
I can't believe my parents
won't buy me one.

04:20.960 --> 04:23.540
They say I can't wear anything
on my body over 500 bucks

04:23.540 --> 04:25.460
unless it's braces.

04:25.460 --> 04:26.460
Oh, there he is.

04:27.750 --> 04:29.250
Don't mention
Teen Help Line.

04:29.250 --> 04:30.880
Or that he wants to say
adios to his vida.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.670
Hey there, Superman.
What's the haps in Metropolis?

04:36.670 --> 04:38.330
Uh, what's going on?

04:38.330 --> 04:39.670
Nothing, muchacho.

04:39.670 --> 04:41.460
We just thought maybe
we should all hang out.

04:41.460 --> 04:43.500
You guys want to hang out
with me?

04:43.500 --> 04:44.670
I know.
Isn't that great?

04:44.670 --> 04:47.210
No. It's the stupidest thing
I've ever heard.

04:47.210 --> 04:49.540
Look, guys,
it's a Wednesday, alright?

04:49.540 --> 04:52.420
A new comic book just dropped,
so take a hike.

04:52.420 --> 04:53.620
But we're gonna
be your friends.

04:53.620 --> 04:55.920
I don't want to be friends
with you morons.

04:55.920 --> 04:57.380
You've got
a stupid face.

04:57.380 --> 04:59.500
And you just
generally suck.

05:03.500 --> 05:05.750
I guess we're just gonna have to
try harder tomorrow.

05:05.750 --> 05:07.080
Let's not be hasty.

05:07.080 --> 05:08.960
Maybe we should let nature
take its course here.

05:08.960 --> 05:14.420
♪♪

05:14.420 --> 05:16.080
I can't believe Mom
changed her mind

05:16.080 --> 05:17.710
and is letting you
be a Wildflower Girl.

05:17.710 --> 05:19.170
She would've never done
that for me.

05:19.170 --> 05:20.540
Well, you didn't
have the benefit

05:20.540 --> 05:22.420
of a terrible older sister
to make you look good.

05:22.420 --> 05:23.460
Yeah.

05:23.460 --> 05:24.920
Wait.

05:24.920 --> 05:26.580
I just got off the phone
with Carnegie Mellon.

05:26.580 --> 05:28.500
There's an alumnus coming
through Westport tomorrow,

05:28.500 --> 05:29.750
and they wanted to move up
your interview.

05:29.750 --> 05:31.500
I said yes.
Why would you
move it up?

05:31.500 --> 05:32.750
Because
you're all prepared.

05:32.750 --> 05:34.290
Plus, it's good
to get in early.

05:34.290 --> 05:35.710
And there's
even better news --

05:35.710 --> 05:37.380
your interview
is with Brecken Phillips.

05:37.380 --> 05:39.420
The Broadway guy?
Yeah, he's an alum.

05:39.420 --> 05:40.710
And your interview's
in the afternoon.

05:40.710 --> 05:43.500
Or, as they say in the theatre,
a matinee.

05:47.750 --> 05:49.290
Just so you know,

05:49.290 --> 05:51.960
people outside this house
think I'm entertaining.

05:54.880 --> 05:56.880
So, you're not ready
at all, huh?

05:56.880 --> 05:59.040
No. I just told Dad I was
to get him off my back.

05:59.040 --> 06:00.120
What am I gonna do?

06:00.120 --> 06:01.710
You're just gonna have to
cram for it.

06:01.710 --> 06:02.830
You're right.

06:02.830 --> 06:04.420
If I can get through
all of "Harry Potter"

06:04.420 --> 06:05.670
in a weekend,
I can do this.

06:05.670 --> 06:09.000
You read all of "Harry Potter"
in one weekend?

06:09.000 --> 06:10.120
It's a book?

06:10.120 --> 06:14.250
♪♪

06:14.250 --> 06:15.830
[ Door opens ]

06:15.830 --> 06:17.750
Girls: Anna-Kat's here!

06:17.750 --> 06:21.080
Katie, it's so great that
Anna-Kat's joining the troop.

06:21.080 --> 06:23.380
Yes, you must be
so relieved

06:23.380 --> 06:25.620
she'll finally have some
positive female role models.

06:25.620 --> 06:27.460
Mm. Don't feel obligated
to stay.

06:27.460 --> 06:29.000
No, I'll be here.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.460
Okay, Wildflower Girls,

06:30.460 --> 06:32.830
let me see
those wildflower smiles.

06:32.830 --> 06:34.460
[ Camera clicks ]

06:34.460 --> 06:35.540
Ah.

06:35.540 --> 06:37.330
The girls are learning
to make egg parachutes

06:37.330 --> 06:40.920
so they can earn
their aeronautics badges.

06:40.920 --> 06:45.210
Now, you already have your
parachute attached to your egg.

06:45.210 --> 06:48.250
Now let's launch them and
watch them float down safely.

06:48.250 --> 06:50.620
Three, two, one.

06:50.620 --> 06:51.670
Liftoff!

06:53.580 --> 06:54.790
Yay!

06:54.790 --> 06:56.670
Great job,
you guys.
Really good.

06:56.670 --> 06:58.960
Hortensia, clean up!

06:58.960 --> 07:00.880
Okay, so badge time.

07:00.880 --> 07:02.170
Badge time?

07:02.170 --> 07:03.960
All of the eggs broke.

07:05.210 --> 07:06.750
Aren't you going to make them
try it until it works?

07:06.750 --> 07:08.080
Why would we?

07:08.080 --> 07:09.830
To teach them about
a job well done.

07:09.830 --> 07:11.380
Ew.

07:11.380 --> 07:13.120
We always hand out badges,
no matter what.

07:13.120 --> 07:13.960
Thank you.

07:13.960 --> 07:15.040
[ Chuckles ]

07:15.040 --> 07:17.830
And this is for you,
little lady.

07:17.830 --> 07:19.790
[ Chuckles ]
Thank you!

07:19.790 --> 07:21.920
Anna-Kat didn't earn
any of those badges.

07:21.920 --> 07:23.500
Oh, relax, Katie.

07:23.500 --> 07:25.380
It looks better for the pictures
if all the girls match.

07:25.380 --> 07:26.710
And what kind of
life lesson is that?

07:26.710 --> 07:28.790
Uh, a perfect one.

07:28.790 --> 07:30.420
Alright, ladies.

07:30.420 --> 07:32.580
Smile like you'll never have
to worry about money.

07:32.580 --> 07:33.920
[ Chuckles ]

07:33.920 --> 07:35.380
Hortensia, snap-snap.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.080
[ Camera clicks ]

07:44.330 --> 07:47.540
I'm gonna pick out some shoes
that go with my new sash.

07:47.540 --> 07:48.460
[ Giggles ]

07:49.960 --> 07:51.080
[ Sighs ]

07:51.080 --> 07:52.580
Greg, what are
you doing?

07:52.580 --> 07:54.170
Uh, reorganizing
the junk drawer.

07:54.170 --> 07:55.330
Ugh.

07:55.330 --> 07:57.880
[ Clatter ]

07:57.880 --> 08:00.000
We've got bigger problems
around here.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.710
They give Anna-Kat's troop
badges for doing nothing.

08:02.710 --> 08:05.250
I had $20 in dimes
stacked up right here.

08:05.250 --> 08:07.170
I can't pull her out
because I promised

08:07.170 --> 08:08.380
she could
be a part of it.

08:08.380 --> 08:10.000
But...
Here we go.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.460
...I am going to host
the next meeting

08:12.460 --> 08:14.460
and teach the girls
how to make lasagna.

08:14.460 --> 08:16.380
Suspiciously wholesome.

08:16.380 --> 08:18.000
And I'll tell the girls
to take off their sashes

08:18.000 --> 08:19.460
so they don't get messy

08:19.460 --> 08:21.040
and then stuff them in
the garbage disposal

08:21.040 --> 08:22.170
and grind 'em up.

08:22.170 --> 08:23.670
There's my girl!

08:23.670 --> 08:25.670
Wouldn't it be more
inspirational for Anna-Kat

08:25.670 --> 08:27.380
if you actually teach
the girls to cook

08:27.380 --> 08:28.710
and make them earn
their cooking badge?

08:29.920 --> 08:31.460
Mm-hmm.
Probably the way to go.

08:32.710 --> 08:34.210
It's good that we workshop
these things.

08:34.210 --> 08:36.080
Hey.
[ Drawer opens ]

08:36.080 --> 08:37.330
Can we get rid of
these phone chargers?

08:37.330 --> 08:39.790
One day, the PalmPilot
is coming back.

08:39.790 --> 08:40.920
And when it does,

08:40.920 --> 08:43.120
you bet your ass
Katie Otto's gonna be ready.

08:44.080 --> 08:45.250
Back in the drawer.

08:45.250 --> 08:50.710
♪♪

08:50.710 --> 08:52.330
What do you think?

08:52.330 --> 08:54.120
I took the laces
out of my Converse.

08:54.120 --> 08:55.120
That's cool, right?

08:55.120 --> 08:56.580
Not now, Anna-Kat.

08:56.580 --> 08:58.500
I'm trying to memorize facts
about Carnegie Mellon.

08:58.500 --> 09:01.120
Did you know there's no such
thing as a Carnegie melon?

09:01.120 --> 09:03.210
I know I told you
to cram,

09:03.210 --> 09:06.170
but turns out you don't
have to work that hard.

09:06.170 --> 09:07.170
What are you
talking about?

09:07.170 --> 09:08.620
At my Wildflower Girls
meeting,

09:08.620 --> 09:11.210
they taught me all you need
to do is show up, smile,

09:11.210 --> 09:12.500
and the world
will deliver.

09:12.500 --> 09:13.830
You're a good smiler.

09:13.830 --> 09:15.790
[ Chuckles ]
I am a good smiler.

09:15.790 --> 09:17.210
There you go.

09:17.210 --> 09:19.040
The bee comes
to the wildflower.

09:19.040 --> 09:20.170
Not the other way around.

09:20.170 --> 09:21.330
So, I'm the bee.

09:21.330 --> 09:22.790
That makes a lot of sense.

09:22.790 --> 09:24.920
No, you're the wildflower.

09:24.920 --> 09:26.790
I'll be honest, I didn't even
get it when I was the bee.

09:26.790 --> 09:32.620
♪♪

09:32.620 --> 09:35.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:35.000 --> 09:36.250
I don't know
about this.

09:36.250 --> 09:38.170
Trevor wasn't into it
last time.

09:38.170 --> 09:39.380
He was just
pushing us away

09:39.380 --> 09:41.540
because he has difficulty
managing his feelings.

09:41.540 --> 09:43.290
Textbook depression.

09:43.290 --> 09:44.920
It's up to us
to follow through.

09:44.920 --> 09:46.920
It could save his life.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.420
If you say so.

09:58.500 --> 09:59.710
Hey, man.

09:59.710 --> 10:01.380
Can't you losers
get your own lives?

10:01.380 --> 10:03.000
We're just letting you know
you're not alone.

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
Yeah, because you two idiots
keep showing up.

10:05.750 --> 10:07.540
Zuckerberg, Gates, Jobs.

10:07.540 --> 10:08.790
What do they all
have in common?

10:08.790 --> 10:10.500
I've been all of them
for Halloween?

10:10.500 --> 10:12.830
No, they were all reclusive
nerds when they were young

10:12.830 --> 10:14.620
and became titans of industry.

10:14.620 --> 10:17.170
I'm harnessing my disdain for
everyone at this crappy school

10:17.170 --> 10:18.920
and using it to fuel
my success later in life.

10:18.920 --> 10:20.500
Later in life?

10:20.500 --> 10:22.670
But you called Teen Help Line.
I talked to you.

10:22.670 --> 10:24.670
I don't even know what
Teen Help Line is.

10:24.670 --> 10:26.000
Now, why don't you
make like

10:26.000 --> 10:27.500
lesser-known original
Justice League character

10:27.500 --> 10:28.750
Martian Manhunter

10:28.750 --> 10:29.960
and disappear?

10:33.500 --> 10:35.460
I could've sworn it was him,
but maybe I was wrong.

10:35.460 --> 10:37.170
Boy: Hey, Justice League,
watch out!

10:37.170 --> 10:38.250
[ Laughter ]
Hey!

10:38.250 --> 10:39.670
Dude, hide behind
my cape!

10:39.670 --> 10:41.040
♪♪

10:41.040 --> 10:42.000
Wait! What about
my jacket?!

10:42.000 --> 10:43.880
Leave it, leave it!

10:43.880 --> 10:45.080
Leave it!

10:45.080 --> 10:46.580
Katie:
Okay, Wildflower Girls,

10:46.580 --> 10:50.420
the trick to making
the perfect lasagna is layering.

10:50.420 --> 10:51.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:51.790 --> 10:53.460
Let's pay attention.

10:53.460 --> 10:56.290
It goes pasta, meat sauce,
cheese, repeat.

10:56.290 --> 10:57.460
Do it with me.

10:57.460 --> 10:59.790
Look, a lion's friends
with a duck.

10:59.790 --> 11:01.330
Aww!
Aww!
Aww!
Aww!

11:01.330 --> 11:03.710
Hello? Who wants
their cooking badge?

11:03.710 --> 11:05.170
I do.

11:05.170 --> 11:06.120
Hortensia?

11:10.540 --> 11:13.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:13.250 --> 11:15.080
[ Groans ]
[ Cellphone rings ]

11:15.080 --> 11:16.830
[ Cellphone beeps ]

11:16.830 --> 11:19.330
Angela, where are you? You said
you were gonna help me.

11:19.330 --> 11:21.040
Ugh, I had to go
to the school.

11:21.040 --> 11:22.830
They accused Sebastian
of plagiarizing

11:22.830 --> 11:25.420
just because he copied
an article he found online.

11:25.420 --> 11:27.670
Unh-unh. I'm going to give that
teacher a piece of my mind.

11:27.670 --> 11:30.330
So, you're mad at the teacher
and not at your son who cheated?

11:30.330 --> 11:32.290
What kind of message
does that send to him?

11:32.290 --> 11:34.380
That Mommy's little baby
does no wrong. Pfft.

11:35.580 --> 11:38.080
Oh, no. I listened
to the wrong friend.

11:38.080 --> 11:39.380
Can we get
our badges now?

11:39.380 --> 11:40.880
No. You can't.

11:40.880 --> 11:43.420
The only person getting a badge
is Hortensia,

11:43.420 --> 11:45.580
because she actually
did the work.

11:45.580 --> 11:47.210
What?! Mom!

11:47.210 --> 11:49.080
I don't like not getting
what I want.

11:49.080 --> 11:49.790
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!

11:49.790 --> 11:52.790
I hate you, Hortensia.

11:52.790 --> 11:55.790
When I close my eyes,
the entire world disappears,

11:55.790 --> 11:58.120
and I am a bird.

11:58.120 --> 11:59.670
Fly, Hortensia.

11:59.670 --> 12:00.750
Fly.

12:00.750 --> 12:04.620
♪♪

12:04.620 --> 12:07.290
I am happy to represent
Carnegie Mellon

12:07.290 --> 12:10.460
because it gave me
the confidence and skills

12:10.460 --> 12:13.380
to do everything
from Stanley Kowalski

12:13.380 --> 12:15.620
to the voice of
bleach-free surface cleaner.

12:15.620 --> 12:17.080
Oh, oh!

12:17.080 --> 12:18.710
[ Cockney accent ]
Stains, get outta here!

12:18.710 --> 12:19.920
[ Normal voice ]
That was you?

12:19.920 --> 12:21.420
[ Giggles ] Yeah.

12:21.420 --> 12:23.170
So, I-I got to tell you,

12:23.170 --> 12:25.830
the -- the music department
was -- was a big fan

12:25.830 --> 12:27.960
of your audition tape,
and so was I.

12:27.960 --> 12:29.170
Cool.

12:29.170 --> 12:31.540
Alright, so, uh,
why do you think

12:31.540 --> 12:33.580
Carnegie Mellon
is the right school for you?

12:33.580 --> 12:34.880
Because of
the music program.

12:34.880 --> 12:37.250
And what aspects
of our music program?

12:38.460 --> 12:40.380
All of them?

12:40.380 --> 12:42.170
Are -- Are --
Are you asking me, or...?

12:42.170 --> 12:44.210
No...?

12:44.210 --> 12:45.750
Okay, alright.
Never mind.

12:45.750 --> 12:49.170
Um, so, where do you see
yourself in 10 years?

12:49.170 --> 12:50.210
At Carnegie Mellon.

12:50.210 --> 12:52.580
Okay, we're
a four-year program, so...

12:52.580 --> 12:54.750
And a great one.
[ Chuckles ]

12:54.750 --> 12:55.960
Yes. Um...

12:55.960 --> 12:58.000
Is there anything else
you'd like to add?

12:58.000 --> 13:02.080
Uh, what you can bring
to -- to Carnegie?

13:02.080 --> 13:04.000
Like a pillow
and comforter and stuff?

13:04.000 --> 13:06.830
No.
Like your philosophy.

13:06.830 --> 13:08.210
Oh!
I have one of those.

13:08.210 --> 13:10.750
Um, I'm gonna
show up, smile,

13:10.750 --> 13:12.250
and the world
will deliver.

13:14.790 --> 13:16.750
[ Sighs ]
The people who made this form

13:16.750 --> 13:18.790
really didn't plan
for someone like you.

13:18.790 --> 13:20.420
[ Chuckles ]

13:20.420 --> 13:22.250
♪♪

13:22.250 --> 13:24.000
What is
going on here?

13:24.000 --> 13:26.040
We all got 911 texts
from our daughters.

13:26.040 --> 13:28.120
Anna-Kat's mom won't
give us our badges.

13:28.120 --> 13:29.960
Katie, give the girls
their badges.

13:29.960 --> 13:32.000
They did nothing
but fool around.

13:32.000 --> 13:33.540
It's okay.
You're new here.

13:33.540 --> 13:35.380
Just hand them over,
and we'll forgive you.

13:35.380 --> 13:37.420
What kind of world
do we live in

13:37.420 --> 13:39.830
where you're so afraid of
disappointing your children?

13:39.830 --> 13:41.580
If they misbehave
or don't listen,

13:41.580 --> 13:43.460
they shouldn't be
rewarded for it.

13:43.460 --> 13:44.670
I don't follow you.
Are you well?

13:45.880 --> 13:47.920
It's never the child's
fault nowadays.

13:47.920 --> 13:50.420
It's always the teacher
or the coach or --

13:50.420 --> 13:53.120
It's fine. You just tell me
when to stop.

13:53.120 --> 13:54.120
No!

13:54.120 --> 13:55.380
This is bigger than money.

13:55.380 --> 13:57.290
Just...
give me the badges!

13:57.290 --> 13:58.710
[ Grunting ]

13:58.710 --> 13:59.750
That's right.
Take it.

13:59.750 --> 14:00.710
Come on.
Use your muscles.

14:00.710 --> 14:02.290
[ Grunts ]

14:02.290 --> 14:04.620
Damn you and
your poor-person strength!

14:04.620 --> 14:06.330
Mom, you're
embarrassing me!

14:06.330 --> 14:08.040
Come on, girls.
We're taking you home.

14:08.040 --> 14:10.250
[ Indistinct talking ]

14:10.250 --> 14:12.000
Katie, if you don't
give the girls

14:12.000 --> 14:14.080
their cooking badges
at the next meeting,

14:14.080 --> 14:15.620
Anna-Kat
is out of the troop.

14:15.620 --> 14:16.500
[ Gasps ]

14:16.500 --> 14:17.880
Yeah, you better go,

14:17.880 --> 14:19.540
because I'm about to earn
my face-slapping badge!

14:19.540 --> 14:20.290
[ Door closes ]

14:24.960 --> 14:27.290
I can't believe
you embarrassed me like that.

14:27.290 --> 14:28.620
[ Sighs ]

14:28.620 --> 14:30.210
You know what?

14:30.210 --> 14:33.170
I'm eating your hidden stash
of 100 Grand bars.

14:33.170 --> 14:35.540
Hey! That's
my plant candy!

14:36.750 --> 14:38.880
Stop. Come here.

14:38.880 --> 14:39.750
Sit down.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.540
I know that you're mad,
but you're a big girl now,

14:44.540 --> 14:47.670
so I'm going to explain to you
why I don't like this troop.

14:47.670 --> 14:49.420
And then I'm going to
let you decide

14:49.420 --> 14:51.000
what you think
that I should do.

14:51.000 --> 14:51.750
Fair?

14:51.750 --> 14:53.080
Fair.

14:54.750 --> 14:56.330
[ Inhales deeply ]

14:56.330 --> 14:58.920
It is a bad lesson
to teach young girls

14:58.920 --> 15:00.670
that you get
something for nothing.

15:00.670 --> 15:02.540
Because outside of
a town like this,

15:02.540 --> 15:05.080
you do nothing,
you get nothing.

15:05.080 --> 15:08.880
You girls are smarter,
stronger, and better than that.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.210
Do you understand?

15:10.210 --> 15:11.000
I do.

15:12.290 --> 15:14.920
I understand that I want you to
give my friends their badges

15:14.920 --> 15:16.330
and stop embarrassing me.

15:22.420 --> 15:23.540
Hey, where'd they go?

15:23.540 --> 15:24.830
Does everyone know?

15:24.830 --> 15:26.380
Seriously, Katie, there was
a lot of candy here

15:26.380 --> 15:27.460
three days ago.

15:27.460 --> 15:28.710
♪♪

15:28.710 --> 15:31.040
Well, it was, uh,
nice meeting you, and, uh,

15:31.040 --> 15:32.880
the admissions department
will be in touch soon.

15:32.880 --> 15:34.540
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

15:34.540 --> 15:36.960
Oh, perfect!

15:36.960 --> 15:39.920
I just wasted my afternoon,
and now I got to call AAA.

15:42.000 --> 15:45.120
I meant..."wasted" in a...
different way than you think.

15:45.120 --> 15:46.210
Oh.

15:46.210 --> 15:47.790
I can change it for you.

15:47.790 --> 15:49.670
[ Chuckles ] You know how
to change a tire?

15:49.670 --> 15:51.000
Yeah. Pop the trunk.

15:53.330 --> 15:54.580
Put on
the parking brake.

15:57.000 --> 15:58.000
Alright.

15:58.000 --> 15:59.040
[ Click ]

16:01.290 --> 16:02.790
Uh, don't you still
need the jack?

16:02.790 --> 16:06.250
You loosen the lug nuts first
so the tire doesn't spin.

16:06.250 --> 16:07.540
Is this a "Parent Trap"
situation?

16:07.540 --> 16:09.620
Did the more pragmatic twin
tag in

16:09.620 --> 16:10.710
while I was
in the bathroom?

16:10.710 --> 16:12.120
No. [ Chuckles ]

16:12.120 --> 16:13.460
Changing a tire
was on my list.

16:13.460 --> 16:14.790
Your list?

16:14.790 --> 16:16.750
I'm working on a life-skills
list before I go to college.

16:16.750 --> 16:17.920
Really?

16:17.920 --> 16:19.460
Yeah, you know...
[ Grunts ]

16:19.460 --> 16:21.830
...things like
how to change a tire,

16:21.830 --> 16:24.790
how balance a checkbook,
how to unclog a toilet.

16:24.790 --> 16:27.000
Do you know flushable wipes
aren't really flushable?

16:27.000 --> 16:29.920
[ Chuckles ]
I did not.

16:29.920 --> 16:33.000
Uh, you know, Taylor,
I-I got to confess,

16:33.000 --> 16:35.080
my impression of you
wasn't stellar.

16:36.620 --> 16:37.960
Oh.

16:37.960 --> 16:40.250
You came off as kind of
a one-dimensional person,

16:40.250 --> 16:42.210
but I think I had you
pegged wrong.

16:42.210 --> 16:45.580
I'd like to hear more about
this list -- and you.

16:45.580 --> 16:48.170
You know, how would you like to
do this interview over again?

16:48.170 --> 16:49.670
That'd be great.

16:49.670 --> 16:51.920
[ Clank ]
Uh, no, no.
Tire first.

16:51.920 --> 16:54.420
[ Both chuckle ]

16:54.420 --> 16:57.380
I'd help, but
I'm a hand double for Shrek.

16:57.380 --> 16:58.620
[ Chuckles ]

16:59.790 --> 17:03.710
♪♪

17:03.710 --> 17:06.210
[ Sighs ] It wasn't Trevor,
so what do we do now?

17:06.210 --> 17:08.880
Let's just forget about it.
You've done everything you can.

17:08.880 --> 17:11.290
Oh, and don't worry about
the incident in the cafeteria.

17:11.290 --> 17:12.960
My PR guy's
already on it.

17:12.960 --> 17:15.790
He had to move a few things
around, but this week,

17:15.790 --> 17:17.290
Derek Jeter's gonna
sit with us at lunch.

17:17.290 --> 17:19.830
Hey, Superman!
Think fast!

17:19.830 --> 17:21.710
Ooh, nice grab!
Alright,
I'll see you at practice.

17:21.710 --> 17:23.460
Oh, my God.

17:23.460 --> 17:25.080
Cooper:
Is Will Hansen Superman?

17:25.080 --> 17:27.000
That's the voice
on the phone.

17:27.000 --> 17:28.460
Why would he want
to end his life?

17:28.460 --> 17:30.960
He's got the sneakers,
the belt, and the watch.

17:30.960 --> 17:32.580
He's rocking full Gucch.

17:32.580 --> 17:34.750
If that's not happiness,
I don't know what is.

17:34.750 --> 17:37.290
Happiness is actually
Gucci sneakers worn by --

17:37.290 --> 17:39.000
Please stop.

17:39.000 --> 17:40.500
...Matt Damon.

17:40.500 --> 17:41.290
[ Sighs ]

17:42.830 --> 17:45.830
♪♪

17:45.830 --> 17:48.330
You guys, I almost blew
my Carnegie Mellon interview,

17:48.330 --> 17:50.040
but then Brecken Phillips
got a flat tire,

17:50.040 --> 17:51.040
and I changed it
for him.

17:51.040 --> 17:52.420
He was
super impressed.

17:52.420 --> 17:53.790
Since when do you know
how to change a tire?

17:53.790 --> 17:55.330
It's on that stupid
life-skills list

17:55.330 --> 17:56.920
Mom and Dad
are forcing her to do.

17:56.920 --> 17:58.420
But that stupid
life-skills list

17:58.420 --> 18:00.620
got me one step closer
to Carnegie Mellon.

18:00.620 --> 18:02.710
They're super annoying,
but maybe Mom and Dad

18:02.710 --> 18:04.330
might actually know what
they're talking about.

18:04.330 --> 18:07.210
Huh. They're always telling me
money doesn't buy happiness.

18:07.210 --> 18:08.710
I thought that was just
poor talk,

18:08.710 --> 18:10.120
but now
I kind of get it.

18:10.120 --> 18:12.290
Are you two saying that
Mom and Dad are sometimes right?

18:13.670 --> 18:14.330
Yeah.

18:15.380 --> 18:17.040
Huh.

18:17.040 --> 18:19.120
I've got to process this
over a Baby Ruth.

18:19.120 --> 18:24.380
♪♪

18:24.380 --> 18:29.540
♪♪

18:29.540 --> 18:30.580
Katie!

18:30.580 --> 18:33.170
I hope you brought something
for the kids.

18:33.170 --> 18:34.880
I did.

18:34.880 --> 18:36.420
Tara: We're so glad.

18:36.420 --> 18:38.500
We like having
Anna-Kat in the troop.

18:38.500 --> 18:41.040
Be a shame if her mother
blew it for her.

18:42.330 --> 18:45.040
Come on up, girls,
and get your badges.

18:45.040 --> 18:46.170
Yeah!
Yay!
[ Giggles ]

18:50.380 --> 18:54.290
♪♪

18:54.290 --> 18:55.420
I don't want this badge.

18:57.330 --> 18:59.000
I didn't earn it.

18:59.000 --> 19:00.880
None of us did.

19:00.880 --> 19:04.960
If you want something,
you have to work for it.

19:04.960 --> 19:06.210
Because in the real world,

19:06.210 --> 19:08.330
you don't just get
everything handed to you.

19:08.330 --> 19:09.710
I mean, what if
your parents

19:09.710 --> 19:12.170
decide to squander
your trust funds

19:12.170 --> 19:13.620
or you want to
marry for love?

19:13.620 --> 19:14.880
[ All gasp ]

19:14.880 --> 19:16.170
It happens, ladies.

19:16.170 --> 19:18.250
And what are
you gonna do then?

19:18.250 --> 19:21.170
We are smarter, stronger,
and better than that.

19:23.670 --> 19:25.670
I'm not trained in CPR!

19:28.080 --> 19:30.830
Window shopping shouldn't
earn me a hiking badge.

19:30.830 --> 19:33.830
I did not successfully
breed a chinchilla.

19:33.830 --> 19:36.330
Ya sabía cocinar lasaña.

19:36.330 --> 19:38.790
From now on, we don't get badges
unless we earn them.

19:38.790 --> 19:40.880
Right, Wildflower Girls?

19:40.880 --> 19:42.500
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!
Yeah!

19:42.500 --> 19:43.460
Badges!

19:43.460 --> 19:45.120
We don't need
no stinking badges!

19:45.120 --> 19:46.330
What do you think
you're doing?!

19:46.330 --> 19:47.880
This is madness!

19:47.880 --> 19:49.920
How much is it gonna take for
you to put those sashes back on?

19:49.920 --> 19:50.750
Hmm?

19:51.960 --> 19:54.580
So, you listened to me?

19:54.580 --> 19:56.000
No.

19:56.000 --> 19:57.920
I listened to
Taylor and Oliver,

19:57.920 --> 19:59.710
who then told me
to listen to you.

19:59.710 --> 20:01.500
And your father said
trickle-down parenting

20:01.500 --> 20:02.790
wouldn't work.

20:02.790 --> 20:06.290
♪♪

20:10.750 --> 20:14.250
Day 6,596
of parenthood.

20:14.250 --> 20:17.040
Even-numbered day.
I get to pick first,
and I choose Oliver.

20:17.040 --> 20:18.290
No! I want Oliver.

20:18.290 --> 20:19.500
Sorry.

20:19.500 --> 20:20.790
It's a crazy turn of events
in three days.

20:20.790 --> 20:21.540
Mm.

20:22.790 --> 20:24.170
[ Door opens ]

20:28.120 --> 20:29.540
I have something
for you.

20:30.790 --> 20:32.830
It's an integrity badge.

20:32.830 --> 20:34.080
Because you earned it.

20:35.540 --> 20:36.540
Thanks, Mom.

20:36.540 --> 20:37.670
Not so fast.

20:38.540 --> 20:40.380
I don't care about
the Baby Ruths so much,

20:40.380 --> 20:42.170
but where are
my 100 Grand bars?

20:43.540 --> 20:44.790
You have 10 seconds.

20:44.790 --> 20:47.500
♪♪
